That same year, he stood out as the youngest participant in the Cooper International Competition, where he won the third prize and the audience prize, which provided the opportunity for him to perform with the Cleveland Orchestra. 2019 meant more accolades, when, at the age of 15, he was the youngest to win Koreaâ€™s IsangYun International Competition, where he also took home two special prizes.

He also participated in the recording of â€œ2020 Young Musicians of Korea,â€ organized by the Korean Broadcasting System and released that November.
